            <h2>THCA and Drug Testing</h2>

            <div class="alert-box red">
              <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è Important Warning</h4>
              <p><strong>THCA use may result in a positive drug test for THC.</strong> Even though THCA is non-psychoactive, your body may convert small amounts to THC, and some tests may detect THCA directly.</p>
            </div>

            <p>Standard drug tests look for THC metabolites (primarily THC-COOH). Because THCA can convert to THC in your body and may cross-react with test antibodies, using THCA products carries significant risk if you're subject to drug testing.</p>

            <div class="info-box gray">
